        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 18 at 7:40PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 739 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles east of Madisonville, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Trinity and Lovelady.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
